# API Specification Generation Prompt

You are a senior backend architect.
Analyze the provided Java Servlet web project and generate a complete API Specification document for frontend-backend integration.

## Objective

The generated specification must allow frontend developers to implement all API calls without reading backend source code.

## For Each API Endpoint

Generate the following information:

### Basic Information

* API Name
* Description
* HTTP Method
* URL Path
* example URL requet

Example:

Method: POST
Path: /api/auth/login
Description: Authenticate user and create session
example /api/auth/login?role=CUSTOMER

### Authentication

Specify:

* Required Role(s)
* Session requirements

Example:

Login Required: Yes
Role: CUSTOMER, ADMIN


### Request Parameters

#### Path Parameters

| Name | Type | Required | Description |
| ---- | ---- | -------- | ----------- |

#### Query Parameters

| Name | Type | Required | Description |
| ---- | ---- | -------- | ----------- |

#### Request Body

Specify each field and provide example body request.

Example:

{
"email": "[user@example.com](mailto:user@example.com)",
"password": "123456"
}


| Field | Type | Required | Description |
| ----- | ---- | -------- | ----------- |

### Response

Do the same as for request parameters.

#### Success Response

Provide:

* HTTP Status Code
* specify each field and provide example response.

Example:

HTTP 200 OK

{
"success": true,
"data": {
"id": 1,
"username": "john"
}
}

### Business Rules

Document any validation rules.

Examples:

* Email must be unique.
* Password length >= 6.
* Food price must be positive.
* User can only modify their own orders.

